Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State has disclosed that 48 people who were infected with the coronavirus (COVID-19) were discharged in the state on Sunday after being freed from the disease. The explained that the patients were 31 males and 17 females including 10 foreign nationals – four Indians, four Americans, two polish, one Brazilian and one Dutch were discharged from the state’s isolation facilities to reunite with the society. A further breakdown of those discharged shows that one patient was discharged from Onikan, eight from Gbagada, 10 from Agidingbi, 14 from Lekki, four from Mainland Infectious Disease Hospital and 11 from Eti-Osa (LandMark) isolation Centres. “With this, the number of COVID19 confirmed cases that have been successfully managed and discharged in Lagos has risen to 1185,” he mentioned.